  "2026-06-26T19:05:47.336Z",codex-codefactor-sdk-cli-20260626,"Evidence: CodeFactor complexity scope now ignores generated standalone loaders, generated standalone launchers, and tests while keeping shipped source files in analysis; create/update unset parsing tables were collapsed into shared metadata to reduce command surface duplication and maintenance cost. Manual temp smoke in /tmp/tmp.XalxjTQCOu passed init, create, update --unset deadline/assignee, package install todos --project, package doctor --project --detail deep, contracts --flags-only, and health --check-only --summary with only telemetry_queue_pending local warning."
  "2026-06-26T20:18:29.140Z",codex,"CodeFactor PR follow-up: user reported the PR detail page still showed 16 found issues after the duplication/generated-marker patch. Inspection showed all 16 were complexity findings on large existing command/SDK files touched by this branch: search, list, config, create, update, and cli-contracts. To remove the PR findings without forcing an unsafe broad command rewrite into the generated-file remediation PR, this branch now narrows its net source diff to the generated-file CodeFactor marker/checklist changes only. pm-arzz remains open for a dedicated staged complexity refactor of those command handlers."
  "2026-06-26T20:54:06.524Z",codex-gpt5,"Implementation kickoff: continuing the dedicated CodeFactor complexity lane after PR #381 narrowed generated-file remediation. Duplicate-safe orientation checked pm search --status all, open/in-progress items, recent PRs, GitHub issue #374, workflow runs, and security/dependency alerts. Related context: pm-fmjy remains the duplication sibling; this pass will keep edits behavior-preserving and verify with focused tests plus coverage/temp smoke."
  "2026-06-26T21:06:15.855Z",codex-gpt5,"Evidence: staged CodeFactor complexity remediation reduced list/search filter hotspots by extracting parsed filter-state predicates and a shared compact filter echo helper. Local tight static check with --max-complexity 40 no longer reports src/cli/commands/search.ts applyFilters, src/cli/commands/list.ts applyFilters, or the former list/search compact-filter duplicate chunk. Verification passed: node scripts/run-tests.mjs test -- tests/unit/commands/list-command.spec.ts tests/unit/commands/search-command.spec.ts (108 tests); pnpm typecheck; pnpm quality:static; node scripts/run-tests.mjs coverage (256 files, 5133 tests, 100/100/100/100); pnpm contracts:check; pnpm security:scan; pnpm audit --audit-level moderate; pnpm changelog:pm:check with pm-changelog 2026.6.20 unchanged; pm health --check-only --summary --json ok; pm validate --check-resolution --check-history-drift --json ok with known pre-existing validate_resolution_missing_fields:258 warning; Sentry/telemetry gate ok with Sentry critical=0 high=0 and telemetry finish_error_rate_pct=0.7; package doctor deep ok; manual temp smoke passed in /tmp/tmp.7WZSBE62MN using isolated PM_PATH/PM_GLOBAL_PATH for init/create/list/search/health/validate. GitHub check: no open PRs; open issue #374 remains an external RELEASE_PAT environment blocker, not a code-side defect in this branch; Dependabot, secret-scanning, security-advisory, and code-scanning alert APIs returned no open alerts."
  "2026-06-26T21:15:13.130Z",codex-gpt5,"PR evidence: PR #382 is green and mergeable at head e442c1302fa4c65bd33696847d6a558a6fd643d5. Required checks passed: CI build, coverage, typecheck, static, compat, smokes, runtime smoke on Ubuntu/macOS, Windows regression, Docs and Skills, CodeQL, CodeFactor, codecov/patch. Available review agents reported clean results: CodeRabbit completed, Cubic reported no issues, Hound passed, CodeFactor passed. Gemini review is temporarily quota-blocked by GitHub bot response, Codex connector is not configured on GitHub, and Sourcery is rate-limited/skipped, so there are no actionable findings from the agents that ran."
